8. Confusion Matrix
cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)

Used to evaluate classification performance.
Matrix contains:
True Positive (TP)
Model predicted Positive, and it is actually Positive
Example:
Patient has disease → model says disease present.
2. True Negative (TN)
Model predicted Negative, and it is actually Negative.
Example:
Patient healthy → model says healthy.
3. False Positive (FP)
Model predicted Positive, but actually Negative.
Example:
Healthy patient → model wrongly says disease present.
Also called Type I Error.
4. False Negative (FN)
Model predicted Negative, but actually Positive.
Example:
Patient has disease → model wrongly says healthy.
Also called Type II Error.
Matrix contains:

Value	Meaning
TN	Correctly predicted 0
FP	Incorrectly predicted 1
FN	Incorrectly predicted 0
TP	Correctly predicted 1
TN, FP, FN, TP = cm.ravel()

Extracts all 4 values.

